<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-10-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-10-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="81" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d81">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Memorandum.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Belgian
                                        Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-10-06"><hi rend="italic">October 6,
                                1902</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>By telegram dated October 6, the Belgian Government instructs the
                            legation of Belgium at Washington to ask the Government of the United
                            States to authorize the American cruiser at Cape Haitien to concert with
                            the consul of Belgium for the protection of common interests in the
                            Bayeux plantation.</p>
                    </div>
